{"questionId":"9076628","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph below represents the variation with time <em>t </em>of the horizontal displacement <em>x </em>of a mass attached to a vertical spring.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4811/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_15.49.15.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP3/ENG/TZ1/11\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The total mass for the oscillating system is 30 kg. For this system</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>determine the initial energy.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>E</em>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;× 30&nbsp;×&nbsp;<em>π</em><sup>2</sup>&nbsp;× 0.8<sup>2</sup><strong>»</strong> = 95&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>J<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow initial amplitude between 0.77 to 0.80, giving range between: 88 to 95 J.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076628","referenceCode":"18M.3.HL.TZ1.11b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"determine the initial energy.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.1 – Simple harmonic motion","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}